# Avandad — Layout Helper · V1.0.0
# =====================================================================
# Optional environment configuration. NOTHING in this file is required
# to boot the app for V1 designer testing — the defaults point at the
# bundled demo inventory and a locally-installed ODA converter is only
# needed if you want to import DWG files (DXF works without it).
#
# Copy this file to ``.env`` if your environment supports it, or set
# the variables in your shell before launching the backend.

# ---- Slab inventory source ------------------------------------------
# Absolute path to a ``clean_slabs.json`` file that overrides the
# in-repo fallback inventory. When unset, the backend uses the real
# project export at ``outputs/slab_ingestion/raw_test/clean_slabs.json``
# and falls back to the demo fixture if that is missing.
# STONELAYOUT_INVENTORY_PATH=/absolute/path/to/clean_slabs.json

# ---- ODA File Converter ---------------------------------------------
# Only needed if you plan to convert DWG plans to DXF. When unset, the
# converter is skipped and DWG uploads are rejected with a clear
# message — DXF uploads work without this.
# ODA_FILE_CONVERTER_PATH=/Applications/ODAFileConverter.app/Contents/MacOS/ODAFileConverter
